# Backlog

One file per task. File name: `TASK-NNN.md` with zero-padded sequential ID (`TASK-001`, `TASK-042`, `TASK-137`). Never reuse an ID.

## Status field

Cached in frontmatter but **not authoritative**. Authoritative state is git + VCS PR API. `ops/checks/verify-task-done.sh` reconciles.

| Status      | Meaning                                                              |
|-------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `todo`      | Written, owner assigned, not yet delegated                           |
| `doing`     | Delegated, PR open, work in flight                                   |
| `blocked`   | Stuck: missing dep, scope breach, founder interrupt, CI red          |
| `done`      | Verified via `verify-task-done.sh`, PR merged, ci-gatekeeper approved|

## Caps

- `doing` ≤ 5 at any time. CTO refuses to delegate a sixth until one closes.
- Active (`todo` + `doing` + `blocked`) ≤ 25. Exceeding triggers archival pass.
- Body ≤ 3 sentences. If longer, split the task.

## Lifecycle

1. CTO writes the task file with `status: todo`, owner from escalation matrix.
2. CTO delegates via Agent-tool using the outbound contract in `docs/cto.md`. Status → `doing`.
3. Subagent opens the PR and writes its inbound contract block as the last action into this file.
4. CTO runs `ops/checks/verify-task-done.sh TASK-NNN`. If every check passes and PR is merged → `done`. Otherwise → `blocked` with `blocked_reason`.
5. After `done` + 7 days post-merge, task compacts to `docs/backlog/archive/YYYY-MM.md` (one line: id, title, commit, pr). Individual file deleted.

## Frontmatter schema

See `TASK-000-template.md` for the canonical template. Required fields:

- `id` — `TASK-NNN`
- `title` — imperative, ≤80 chars
- `status` — one of `todo | doing | blocked | done`
- `owner` — subagent name from escalation matrix
- `depends_on` — list of task IDs; may be empty
- `files_allowlist` — globs the subagent is permitted to touch
- `must_not_touch` — globs the subagent must not touch (protected paths default included)
- `acceptance_criteria` — testable bullets; each should name a symbol, file, or observable behavior
- `pr` — PR number, filled when opened
- `commit` — short SHA of merge commit, filled on verification
- `ci_status` — `pending | approved | failed | not_applicable`
- `blocked_reason` — string when `status: blocked`, else null
- `created` — ISO date
- `last_verified` — ISO timestamp, updated by `verify-task-done.sh`
- `escalate_to` — list of subagent names for review; pulled from escalation matrix

## Archive format

`docs/backlog/archive/YYYY-MM.md` is append-only. One line per archived task:

```
- TASK-042 — Add webhook idempotency check — commit abc1234 — pr #17
```

No frontmatter. Full history lives in git; this file is a human-readable index.

## Anti-drift rules

- **No status field written without verification.** If CTO cannot run `verify-task-done.sh`, status stays at its last verified value.
- **No task manufactured by CTO alone.** Every new task traces to founder input or a founder-approved plan file.
- **No direct edits to `done` tasks.** If a `done` task needs revision, open a new task that supersedes it.
- **No renaming of task IDs.** If a task is wrong, mark it `blocked` with `blocked_reason: superseded-by-TASK-NNN` and open a new one.

